ging him closer to his child and ultimately making him fall head over heels in love with her.","poster_path":"/9IToY3FhrwpT3dmKfKjUottl5ci.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[10751],"popularity":0.0936,"release_date":"2025-10-10","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":5.0,"vote_count":4}]},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":4878578,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Sam L. Green","original_name":"Sam L. Green","popularity":0.0071,"profile_path":null,"known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/2W6ihIymHl9GvjnzkBwT26OfSPd.jpg","id":1328183,"title":"Jane is OK","original_title":"Jane is OK","overview":"A young filmmaker navigates her transition while living in an abusive household. Personal videos document several years of isolation as she says goodbye to old friends and welcomes new ones she meets online.","poster_path":"/zquYD7WXNRL7vQ6K9YaXNlCcALZ.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[99,18],"popularity":0.0387,"release_date":"2024-08-16","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":10.0,"vote_count":1}]},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":5624362,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Sam Green","original_name":"Sam Green","popularity":0.0071,"profile_path":null,"known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"id":58291,"name":"Monster TV","original_name":"Monster TV","overview":"Monster TV was a children's television comedy drama about three children who run a TV show in their basement called \"Monster TV\", with monsters Herbert and Rocky as the stars. Little information was published about the show online.","poster_path":null,"media_type":"tv","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[],"popularity":0.1389,"first_air_date":"1999-12-10","softcore":false,"vote_average":0.0,"vote_count":0,"origin_country":["GB"]}]},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":4930215,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Sam Green","original_name":"Sam Green","popularity":0.0,"profile_path":null,"known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"id":1353918,"title":"David Gilbert - A Lifetime of Struggle","original_title":"David Gilbert - A Lifetime of Struggle","overview":"This is a rare opportunity to go behind prison walls for a discussion with David Gilbert, a lifelong anti-imperialist activist and former member of the Weather Underground Organization. David is now serving a life sentence in prison for activities in support of the Black Liberation Movement. He explains why he joined the movement, what led him to go underground, and frankly discusses the strengths and errors of the movement and the WUO.","poster_path":null,"media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[],"popularity":0.0,"release_date":"2017-07-22","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":0.0,"vote_count":0}]},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":4667236,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Sam Cavalli-Green","original_name":"Sam Cavalli-Green","popularity":0.0,"profile_path":null,"known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/CatzqMxuwPER4JBLqVcepf1X1N.jpg","id":960,"name":"Knowing Me Knowing You with Alan Partridge","original_name":"Knowing Me Knowing You with Alan Partridge","overview":"Knowing Me Knowing You with Alan Partridge is a BBC Television series of six episodes, and a Christmas special in 1995. It is named after the song \"Knowing Me, Knowing You\" by ABBA, which was used as the show's title music.\n\nSteve Coogan played the incompetent but self-satisfied Norwich-based host, Alan Partridge. Alan was a spin-off character from the spoof radio show On the Hour. Knowing Me Knowing You was written by Coogan, Armando Iannucci and Patrick Marber, with contributions from the regular supporting cast of Doon Mackichan, Rebecca Front and David Schneider, who played Alan's weekly guests. Steve Brown provided the show's music and arrangements, and also appeared as Glen Ponder, the man in charge of the house band.\n\nThe show was a parody of a chat show. It featured a live audience whose laughter meant that viewers could not mistake the show for a real chat show. Alan went on to appear in two series of the sitcom I'm Alan Partridge, following his life after both his marriage and TV career come to an end.","poster_path":"/4mr2xRXoz8NoWu0oIUYXcnMgKLW.jpg","media_type":"tv","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[35,10767],"popularity":1.9526,"first_air_date":"1994-09-16","softcore":false,"vote_average":7.765,"vote_count":68,"origin_country":["GB"]}]},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":1677572,"known_for_department":"Art","name":"Sam Greenmun","original_name":"Sam Greenmun","popularity":0.105,"profile_path":null,"known_for":[{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/zsgdVbuEwqZbnUN9qLGEMBYf2Zo.jpg","id":277,"title":"Underworld","original_title":"Underworld","overview":"Vampires and werewolves have waged a nocturnal war against each other for centuries. But all bets are off when a female vampire warrior named Selene, who's famous for her strength and werewolf-hunting prowess, becomes smitten with a peace-loving male werewolf, Michael, who wants to end the war.","poster_path":"/zsnQ41UZ3jo1wEeemF0eA9cAIU0.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[14,28,53],"popularity":6.5003,"release_date":"2003-09-19","softcore":false,"video":false,"vote_average":6.849,"vote_count":6582},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/kJJxRr7OHo6UPNXZI89DoIu6Eov.jpg","id":12594,"title":"Wishmaster 2: Evil Never Dies","original_title":"Wishmaster 2: Evil Never Dies","overview":"During a failed art heist, the Djinn is once again liberated. This time, to complete the 1001 wishes that he needs before the final 3, he lets himself go to prison, where he starts his evil reign twisting the hopes of the prisoners. Meanwhile, the woman who set him free accidentally, Morgana, tries to find a way to stop him, aided by a young priest.","poster_path":"/1yb89Er5FyBoAWR1RUIA1p3BNid.jpg","media_type":"movie","original_language":"en","genre_ids":[14,27],"popularity":2.2601,"release_date":"1999-03-12","softcore":false,"vid